<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">chrisstauf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am preparing to lead a Ixiblat raid on thursday and would like to have myself as well as my people as prepared as possible. I am trying to compile a Dossier and strategy for Ixiblat prior to our raid. Here is what I have so far:<P>Ixiblat Fer<BR>Level 61-62<BR>Approx 32k HPs<BR>Hits for 575 max (does he double/triple/quad???)<BR>AE Fire 200-300dmg (easily resisted)<P>Strategy:<BR>Pull Naxot to Skyfire zone and keep mezzed<BR>Turn in the shell<BR>Ixiblat spawns<BR>Pull Ixiblat to Skyfire zone<BR>fight him there<P>Fighting Strategy:<BR>It sounds like the key is Mage fire pets in mass quantities<BR>Have tank groups with 2 clerics in each<BR>Have caster groups with 1 cleric in each<BR>Send in fire pets first with enchanter charmed wurms<BR>get a shaman to land slow on him<BR>Send in tanks at 80-90% health<BR>Casters nuke at 20-30%<P>Is there anything you would change to this? I have heard of a tactic of getting a warrior with riposte discipline to engage him first for about 20 seconds while clerics chain CH him, while the shamans are getting a slow to land....is this a better tactic?<P>I estimate we will have a fighting force of around 7 groups with an avg level of 52.<P><P>------------------<BR>Chrisstauf HealingSoul<BR>Priest of Light of the Karana Lightbringers<BR>51 times blessed by Mithaniel Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chain CHs only work if you have a level 60 warrior since only a 60 warrior would be successful at keeping agro (it's not impossible with a 55+ war, but it's harder without the ability to taunt 60+ mobs).<P>I would HIGHLY recommend a 60 shaman since they have the best chance at landing slow.<P>Level 49 mage fire pets are quite useful here...<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>Erudite Templar of Prexus<BR>Cohort Chalybeius<BR>Cazic Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">chrisstauf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What types of spells work good against him when he gets low on life? Summon DD's, Lure, IC, etc??<P>------------------<BR>Chrisstauf HealingSoul<BR>Priest of Light of the Karana Lightbringers<BR>51 times blessed by Mithaniel Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">KinekorEQ</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Need a high level shaman 59-60 or high level chanter 59-60 to have a good chance for Slow to land.  If you don't slow you have a great chance of being wiped.  Shaman or Chanter will probably get summoned and die after slowing.  <P>Have only one main tank taunt, and make sure that all healers have a hotkey to target the main tank and have everyone keep them healed.  Using Rune on the tank also help.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">fredd999</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Last time we fought him , 55 Wizard friend of mine hit for full with his level 52 Lure spell everytime.<P>I hear he is not very fire resistant.<P>As for the main tank engaging first, I had a 60 Pally.  He needed his first heal pretty quick, Cast Divine Light, I got summoned and diced.<P>Second time, He used lay Hands for first heal, I healed him -> summoned, DA, Healed -->summoned DB, etc. other Cleric had same problem, but the Pally could not keep agro.  Sounds like the advice above about the 60 Warrior is the way to go.  Other than that lots of Mage Fire Pets sounds good too.  Will have to try that next time.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jhihad</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ixiblat fight is very straightforward.  I would suggest not wasting time charming wurms.  Just go full blast on him, he hits pretty hard but wiht only 32K hp he goes down VERY fast.  Just pull to SF zone and have all your melee attack all together using offensive disciplines.  Casters should nuke soon after melee go in.  Its very important that your casters know not to run Ixiblat around.  Stick to quick heals like divine light.  I would suggest healing as soon as you see someone health bar start to drop, often if you wait till the health is halfway its too late.  Ixiblat is slowable, so get a tash and hopefully a lvl 60 shaman and the fight is a breeze.<P>One other thing, Ixiblat AE is a joke, its nothing compared to its melee dmg output.  Make sure everyone goes full AC/HP gear rather than Fire resist gear.  Also High lvl mage fire pets will dispell, which is what you dont want happen against Ixiblat if you are trying to land slow.  Go with Air/Water mage pet, he ignores pets for the most part anyway so get a good dmg dealer.<BR>------------------<BR>Jhihad Daemonwrath, High Priest<BR>Xanit K'ven, Vallon Zek<p>[This message has been edited by Jhihad (edited 05-25-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">chrisstauf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thank you all for your help and input. We just went straight out attack (no wurms) and took him down 4 times out of 4 attempts.<P><P>------------------<BR>Chrisstauf HealingSoul<BR>Priest of Light of the Karana Lightbringers<BR>51 times blessed by Mithaniel Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tiggi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Congrats on your success with Ixiblat. I'm interested to know whether you used your original strategy posted here or whether you modified it as a result of the postings?<P>I'm asking because I myself need to set up an Ixiblat raid now and want to piggy back on your success!<P>Tiggi Nightingale<BR>Cleric of the 54th Circle<BR>Guild Chancellor & Advisor<BR>Feaduath Eldaren ~ Tarew Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zuht</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">btw, you can't have more than 4 pets attacking, the rest just... won't =)  Slow makes this easy, but we did it 5 times in a row with no slow... so it's not required.  The AE is a joke, but the melee is QUITE a shock if you have not fought some of the nastier Velious mobs or their like.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
